  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana has recently become one of the new areas where genetically modified organisms (GMOs) are being tested, which threatens their culture, rights, food sovereignty and puts them at risk for corporate capture. Because of this, the Ghana National Civil Society Networks has solicited funds to organize a meeting to analyze the impacts the introduction of GMOs would have on the food security of rural farmers in Ghana, to provide information in support of advocacy around the issue of GMOs, and to develop a shared position and strategy to protect peasant farmers from the impacts of GMOs. Participants will include farmers, members of the various networks, CSOs, media, academia and researchers.</narrative>
  </description>
